Preheat the oven (for the buns) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 (you can also warm
the buns in the #toaster{}).

Boil a #pot{} of @water{about 2%l} with @salt{to taste} for the potatoes.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} (quarter larger pieces).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water, lower the heat to medium and cook
until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced) as thinly
as possible.

Pop into a #small bowl{} along with the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet}, @salt{1/4%tsp}
and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Toss to coat then set aside, continuing to stir occasionally.

Drain before serving.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled) and coarsely grate (unpeeled).

To make the slaw, toss the carrot with @gochujang paste{1%sachet}(use less if you don't
like spice), @ketchup{2%sachets} and @aioli{1/2%sachet}. Season to taste with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}(thinly sliced).

Trim the @salad leaves{120%g}. Reserve one leaf per burger and thinly slice the
rest.

Just before serving, toss the chopped salad leaves with the @aioli{1/2%sachet}
and half the drained onion. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @prawns{180%g} and season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Cook until pink on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are cooked
> when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked, stir through a knob of @butter{to taste} and the
@paprika{2%sachets}.

Toss to coat then season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} onto a #baking tray{}. Warm in the #oven{}, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Place a salad leaf on each bun base.

Load on the sliced tomato, remaining pickled onion, carrot slaw and prawns.

Sandwich your burger closed with the top bun.

Serve the paprika butter potatoes alongside.